From: ETNA Workload Synthesizer <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sat, 02 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Synthesized: dropFinal empty list crash bug
 (after 6da4473ce648485317c613b84c8a327a796f8496)

Historical context: commit 6da4473 added the missing
`dropFinal _ [] = []` clause; before that fix, `dropFinal DropBlank
[]` evaluated `last []` and crashed at runtime. A later refactor
(cbc3c5f, "fix space leak") rewrote dropFinal to use a recursive
helper, which independently handles the empty case via
`dropFinal' [] = []`. Reverting just one safety net no longer
reproduces the historical crash on modern HEAD, so this patch
reverses both -- restoring the original `last l / init l`
formulation that crashes on an empty SplitList.

The `+++` side is modern HEAD (fixed); the `---` side is the
historical buggy formulation. `git apply -R` installs the bug.
---
 src/Data/List/Split/Internals.hs | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/Data/List/Split/Internals.hs b/src/Data/List/Split/Internals.hs
--- a/src/Data/List/Split/Internals.hs
+++ b/src/Data/List/Split/Internals.hs
@@ -245,7 +245,12 @@ dropInitial _ l = l

 -- | Drop a final blank chunk according to the given 'EndPolicy'.
 dropFinal :: EndPolicy -> SplitList a -> SplitList a
-dropFinal DropBlank l | Text [] <- last l = init l
+dropFinal _ [] = []
+dropFinal DropBlank l = dropFinal' l
+ where
+  dropFinal' [] = []
+  dropFinal' [Text []] = []
+  dropFinal' (x : xs) = x : dropFinal' xs
 dropFinal _ l = l

 -- * Combinators
